headline: Trump: strong dollar sounds good but 'you make a hell of a lot more' with a weaker one
summary: WASHINGTON (Reuters) -U.S. President Donald Trump said on Friday he liked a strong dollar but "you make a hell of a lot more money" with a weaker one.  The dollar index, which measures the greenback's strength against six major currencies, steadied on Friday after hitting two-week lows earlier in the week.  It is still down roughly 10% over the six months Trump has been in office.
